###  The proof of the `cons_trivial_omega_contra` is completed with `by_contradiction`. 

```lean
theorem cons_trivial_omega_contra {α} [DecidableEq α] {f : ℕ → α} [Function.Injective f] :
    ∀ (w : ℕ), w ∈ (Set.range f) → (w ∉ ∅) := by
  intro w hw
  have h : w ∈ Set.range f := hw
  -- Since w is in the range of f, it is not in the empty set
  have h₁ : w ∉ (∅ : Set α) := by
    intro h₂
    -- If w were in the empty set, it would contradict the fact that it is in the range of f
    exfalso
    simp_all [Set.mem_range]
    <;> aesop
  exact fun h₂ => by simpa using h₁ h₂
```
